==English==

===Pronunciation===
*yo͞ost to͞o, /juːst tu/, /<tt>ju:st tu<tt>/<!--note: the final "u" deliberately has no ː/: symbol after it in IPA and SAMPA-->
*{{audio|en-us-used_to.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adverb===
'''[[used]] [[to]]''' (''negative'' '''[[usedn't to|usedn’t to]]''')

# [[Accustomed]] to; in the [[habit]] of
#:''I am '''used to''' cleaning up other people’s mess.''
# [[formerly|Formerly]]; once, but no longer
#:''I '''used to''' be undecided, but now I’m not so sure.''

====Usage notes====
{{unreferenced}}
'''Used to''' comes from an older usage of the verb '''to [[use]]'''.  Strictly speaking, therefore, “I didn’t use to ...”, “Did you use to ...?” are more correct than the more common forms, “I didn’t used to”, “Did you used to ...?”.  “Usedn’t to”, “Used you to ...?” are more correct than “usen’t to”, “use you to ...?”, however.

